    <id>https://doi.org/10.1287/opre.2025.1769</id>
    <title>Capacity Investment Decisions in Equilibrium: A Distributionally Robust Approach</title>
    <updated>2026-05-22T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Ibrahim Abada, Julien Ancel</name>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;b&gt;Operations Research&lt;/b&gt; &lt;br&gt;Investing in Electricity Production Assets Under Price AmbiguityHow should investors set their capacity when market prices, which determine the revenues of their assets, are ambiguous? In Capacity Investment Decisions in Equilibrium: A Distributionally Robust Approach, Abada and Ancel focus on European electricity markets and argue that the past distribution of prices is no longer trustworthy in crisis regimes such as those recently observed. Leveraging the distributionally robust optimization framework, the authors provide a novel and tractable formulation of the stochastic capacity expansion problem under price ambiguity in a power economy, leading to an equilibrium framework. They prove existence and show that their framework is compatible with the economic theory of pure and perfect competition. Through simulations, they quantify the detrimental impact of ambiguity on system welfare and installed capacity and estimate how certain contracts could help mitigate these effects.</content>
